This paper is primarily focused on the energy and carbon footprints of machine learning research, which falls under the category of "Learning" in computer science. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses strategies for mitigation of carbon emissions and reduction of energy consumption, which could fall under the categories of "Computer Engineering" (cs.CE), "Software Engineering" (cs.SE), "Cybersecurity" (cs.CY), and "Systems and Control" (cs.SY).
